1 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES - FLOOR VERSION
2 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
3 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
4 HOUSE
RESOLUTION 1047 By: Sneed
5
6
7
8 AS INTRODUCED
9 A Resolution emphasizing the State's interest in
CompSource Mutual Insurance Company; recognizing the
10 existence of CompSource Mutual Insurance Company as
an entity ensuring compensation under current
11 workers' compensation law; emphasizing that all
monies and assets of CompSource Mutual Insurance
12 Company are held in trust; and emphasizing the
public's interest in CompSource Mutual Insurance
13 Company.
14
15
16 WHEREAS, CompSource Oklahoma was allowed by the Legislature to
17 become a mutual insurance company, CompSource Mutual Insurance
18 Company, effective January 1, 2015, for the purpose of insuring
19 employers against liability for compensation under the
20 Administrative Workers' Compensation Act, the Oklahoma Workers'
21 Compensation Code, and previous workers' compensation laws; and
22 WHEREAS, because of the State Insurance Fund, the predecessor of
23 CompSource Mutual Insurance Company, was created with taxpayer
24
